Cape Town &ndash; More tremors have hit South Africa on Monday evening &ndash; this time it was felt in Johannesburg, Pretoria, Bloemfontein and Durban.According the US Geological Survey, an earthquake was registered in&nbsp;Moijabana north west of Gaborone at 19:40.A 27-year-old woman from Durban told News24: "My whole bed was shaking. It was so scary. I didn't know what was happening. Then the whole building was shaking. We heard about the tremor in Johannesburg this morning and now it's here!" It was reportedly also felt in Bloemfontein.@margiedgander @khayadlanga Yep I felt in Bloemfontein...!It was also felt in Harare in Zimbabwe. Is it only me or there's just been tremors in Harare?&mdash; rasta interpreter (@percyzvomuya) April 3, 2017 An earth tremor which hit parts of Gauteng and the North West on Monday morning was recorded at 4.6 magnitude.&nbsp;It originated near a gold mining area in Klerksdorp, in the North West.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.